rComments: The class layout was super easy to succeed, I followed the provided rubrics and ended up with a 4.0 in the class, her lecture slides are extremely detailed that you barely need the textbook. She's very helpful in office hours and gave interesting lectures, only thing is she had to many guest lecturers.

Her lecture slides do not have enough information so you do need to attend the lectures and read the textbook. However, her lectures are pretty boring and she does not really explain the material in detail. I feel like, a lot of the content was repetitive. Get ready to attend class and take detailed notes + do a lot of readings!!

I took her for Canadian Politics and the course was kinda meh, it was a year course so she ran out of things to say the second semester. Her lectures are good to be at although she wanders off about random numbers and statistics that you don't have to know. the Tutorials were fun to be at, also do the readings im silly.
